communications.communication:
To Whom It May Concern:

Pursuant to the Freedom of Information Act, I hereby request the following records:

Office of Foreign Asset Control (OFAC) administrative records (designation packages) supporting the designations of the former Paraguayan president Horacio Manuel Cartes Jara and former vice president Hugo Adalberto Velazquez Moreno.

OFAC's announcement of the designations can be found at the following link: https://home.treasury.gov/news/press-releases/jy1221

If any part of these documents are exempt from disclosure, please be sure to review and release all reasonably segregable nonexempt portions of responsive documents, as the FOIA requires.

The requested documents will be made available to the general public, and this request is not being made for commercial purposes.

In the event that there are fees, I would be grateful if you would inform me of the total charges in advance of fulfilling my request. I would prefer the request filled electronically, by e-mail attachment if available or CD-ROM if not.

Thank you in advance for your anticipated cooperation in this matter. I look forward to receiving your response to this request within 20 business days, as the statute requires.

Sincerely,

Matthew Petti

communications.subject: Freedom of Information Act Request: Osama Bin Laden Records
communications.communication:
To Whom It May Concern:

Pursuant to the Freedom of Information Act, I hereby request the following records:

1). Copies of any property records (deeds, financial, construction, etc.) collected of the residence/ compound where Osama Bin Laden was killed, also known as House No 3, Street No 8-A, Garga Road, Thanda Chowa, Hashmi Colony, Abbottabad with the coordinates 34°10'09.6"N 73°14'32.8"E. 

2). Copies of any photographs or video (via on the ground, satellite, aircraft) of the above listed residence that was taken between 2003-2012.

3). Copies of any photographs or video of the body of Osama Bin Laden taken between May 1, 2011 thru May 4, 2011 at any location. It's been indicated in court filings in 2012 that the CIA is in possession of 52 potential records that include photographs and video related to Osama Bin Laden's body (presumably deceased). Article cited for reference: https://www.rcfp.org/judge-denies-request-bin-laden-death-photos-and-video/

4). Any records pertaining to the DNA testing of Osama Bin Laden.

The requested documents will be made available to the general public, and this request is not being made for commercial purposes.

In the event that there are fees, I would be grateful if you would inform me of the total charges in advance of fulfilling my request. I would prefer the request filled electronically, by e-mail attachment if available or CD-ROM if not.

Thank you in advance for your anticipated cooperation in this matter. I look forward to receiving your response to this request within 20 business days, as the statute requires.

Sincerely,

Charles Kallas
